---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Learn | Kreativ Sound"
  description="Practical sound design articles, workflows, and product-guided ideas from Kreativ Sound."
  canonical="https://kreativsound.com/learn/"
  activeNav="learn"
  ogImage="https://kreativsound.com/assets/thumbs/bioforms.jpg"
>
  <section class="card page-main learn-page">
    <div class="learn-hero">
      <div class="learn-hero-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">Learn</p>
        <h1 class="page-title">Short workflow guides for real sound design work.</h1>
        <p class="page-lead">Practical ideas tied to actual packs, with less theory and more direct use cases.</p>
      </div>
      <a class="learn-featured" href="/posts/how-to-use-audio-alchemy-free-2026-04-02.html">
        <img class="learn-featured-image" src="/apps/audio-alchemy/ui/audio-alchemy-mark.svg" width="256" height="256" alt="Audio Alchemy guide artwork" />
        <div class="learn-featured-copy">
          <span class="learn-card-kicker">Featured guide</span>
          <h2>How to Use Audio Alchemy Free</h2>
          <p>Get better results by choosing the right source sounds and using the two bias controls with restraint.</p>
          <span class="learn-card-link">Read guide <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></i></span>
        </div>
      </a>
    </div>

    <section class="learn-section">
      <div class="learn-section-head">
        <h2>Latest Guides</h2>
        <p>Fast reads with direct musical use.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="learn-grid">
        <a class="learn-card" href="/posts/how-to-use-audio-alchemy-free-2026-04-02.html">
          <img class="learn-card-image" src="/apps/audio-alchemy/ui/audio-alchemy-mark.svg" width="160" height="160" alt="Audio Alchemy guide artwork" />
          <time datetime="2026-04-02">April 2, 2026</time>
          <h3>How to Use Audio Alchemy Free</h3>
          <p>Use short source sounds and small control moves for stronger preset results.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="learn-card" href="/posts/how-to-shape-vital-presets-for-dark-motion-2026-03-27.html">
          <img class="learn-card-image" src="/assets/thumbs/velvet-ruins.jpg" width="160" height="160" alt="VELVET RUINS artwork" />
          <time datetime="2026-03-27">March 27, 2026</time>
          <h3>How to Shape Vital Presets for Dark Motion</h3>
          <p>Build motion in Vital without losing weight or clarity.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="learn-card" href="/posts/crafting-ambient-textures.html">
          <img class="learn-card-image" src="/assets/thumbs/bioforms.jpg" width="160" height="160" alt="Ambient textures guide artwork" />
          <time datetime="2026-03-16">March 16, 2026</time>
          <h3>Crafting Ambient Textures</h3>
          <p>A short workflow for building space without overcrowding the mix.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="learn-card" href="/posts/how-to-use-tectonic-2-for-low-end-pressure-2026-03-14.html">
          <img class="learn-card-image" src="/assets/thumbs/tectonic-2.jpg" width="160" height="160" alt="TECTONIC 2 artwork" />
          <time datetime="2026-03-14">March 14, 2026</time>
          <h3>How to Use TECTONIC 2 for Low-End Pressure</h3>
          <p>Keep the low end heavy without making the whole track collapse.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="learn-card" href="/posts/how-to-layer-bioforms-for-organic-motion-2026-03-14.html">
          <img class="learn-card-image" src="/assets/thumbs/bioforms.jpg" width="160" height="160" alt="BIOFORMS artwork" />
          <time datetime="2026-03-14">March 14, 2026</time>
          <h3>How to Layer BIOFORMS for Organic Motion</h3>
          <p>Use one layer for tone and one for movement.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="learn-card" href="/posts/three-ways-to-use-neolith-for-cinematic-tension-2026-03-14.html">
          <img class="learn-card-image" src="/assets/thumbs/neolith.jpg" width="160" height="160" alt="NEOLITH artwork" />
          <time datetime="2026-03-14">March 14, 2026</time>
          <h3>3 Ways to Use NEOLITH for Cinematic Tension</h3>
          <p>Three focused ways to hold pressure without filling everything.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="learn-section">
      <div class="learn-section-head">
        <h2>What Learn Covers</h2>
        <p>Built around practical use, not long theory.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="learn-pillars">
        <article class="learn-pillar">
          <span class="learn-card-kicker">Workflows</span>
          <h3>Product-specific use</h3>
          <p>Guides that help move from browsing presets to actually using them inside cues, beds, and transitions.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="learn-pillar">
          <span class="learn-card-kicker">Focus</span>
          <h3>Tension, space, and motion</h3>
          <p>Short breakdowns around atmosphere, low-register movement, restrained layering, and cinematic pressure.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="learn-pillar">
          <span class="learn-card-kicker">Style</span>
          <h3>Useful, not academic</h3>
          <p>Creative notes that stay direct enough to use in film, ambient, and experimental production sessions.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
